@node Why "Why MultiRead?"
@{i}Why MultiRead?@{ui}

Ever since I got my Amiga, I have used directory manager programs.  From Disk
Master to DirOpus, to MTool I have tried to find programs which make it easy to
perform file operations and make it easy to view pictures or play sounds from a
list of files.  One thing I've always hated, however, was clicking on
text files from ProWrite and FinalWriter.  All I would get was a binary output
of an IFF file.  From this came the idea for MultiRead.

MultiRead takes as an argument the name of a file in ProWrite or FinalWriter
format.  It then dumps the file, in plain English (or whatever the language!) to
the output device.  This way, you can view a text file without the necessity of
starting the actual word processor program.
@endnode

@node How "How does it work?"
@{i}How does it work?@{ui}

MultiRead has only one required argument: the input filename.  By default the
plain text is dumped to the console.  The text is wrapped (default 80 columns)
unless specified no wrap, and the number of columns can be changed.  It is also
possible to either dump to an output file, console, or both.  MultiRead
automatically determines the format of the file, and fails if it is not a
recognized type.
@endnode

@node Usage "MultiRead Usage"
@{i}MultiRead Usage@{ui}

The template for MultiRead is:
@{b}FILE/A,TO=AS/K,NODISPLAY=ND/S,SAVE/S,NOWRAP/S,COLUMNS=CO/N@{ub}

This can be called up by typing "MultiRead ?" at the command line.

The arguments are used as follows:
FILE:        (String) The filename of the input file.
TO:          (String) The filename of the output file if this is desired.
NODISPLAY:   (Switch) Controls whether of not anything goes to the console.
SAVE:        (Switch) Specifies that the text will be saved.  If no filename
                      is specified with "TO" then filename.out will be used.
NOWRAP:      (Switch) Dumps the text with no carriage returns except after
                      paragraphs.  Useful if the text will be imported into
                      another program.
COLUMNS:     (Number) At which column word wrap will take effect.  Defaults to
                      80.
@endnode

@node Author "About the author"
@{i}About the author@{ui}

Hmmm, not much to say.  I've been writing C programs for my Amiga for several
years now.  This my second program which I've felt actually ready for 
distribution.

I also enjoy music, reading, and writing.  I love my Amiga, but not to the
point of fanatacism, and I love programming on it.  I enjoy talking to others
that are the same way.

As for other work I've done, if anyone has the Xetec American Heritage
Illustrated Encyclopedic Dictionary CDROM and cannot run it from WB (I can't
on my @{"system" link System}), I wrote a pretty good program for viewing words and definitions.
It's WorkBench-friendly, saves to the clipboard or another file, prints,
and has a GUI, or shell based interface in the same program for about 20k!

I am also the creator of EasyWB (util/dir/EasyWB14.lha), a program to allow
you to drop files on an AppIcon to launch programs based on pre-defined data
formats and programs.

To get in touch,

My email address is:  arian.kulp@mci.com

or USPS address: Arian T. Kulp
                 705 7th Ave
                 Coralville, IA  52241

and my phone number is: 319/351-0622

I love to hear from other Amiga owners, especially programmers.
@endnode

@node System "My system"
My system consists of an Amiga 2000 with A2620 card (screaming 14Mz 68020
card with a blazing 14Mz 68881 math co-processor), OS3.1, a whopping 2x speed
Reno Mediavision CDROM drive, LineLink (sit down for this) 14.4k modem 
(with fax, of course), external Pyramid MIDI interface, 6 megs of Fast RAM,
1 complete meg of Chip RAM, and a 120M SCSI HD.  (Oh yeah, and 2 (two) @{b}low-
density@{ub} floppy drives)
@endnode

@node Todo "To Do"
@{i}Things to do@{ui}

My FinalWriter and ProWrite handling is where I want it to be right now, but
I still don't have tab support.  This is interpretted as one character, and
when the console displays it, it is expanded thereby messing up the line
wrapping.  With NOWRAP on, it is not really a problem, but I will be fix
this and include a TABSIZE option in an upcoming release to replace the
tabs with spaces.  Paginating options would also be nice (lines per page,
margins, page numbers, etc.).

I would also like to add FTXT (IFF text) support.  Most text programs use
this for clipboard writing only, but it could still come in handy sometimes.
@endnode

